all_answers.question: Competitive exclusion principle definition biology
all_answers.subject: Biology
all_answers.text: Competitive exclusion principle. In ecology the competitive exclusion principle, sometimes referred to as Gause's Law is a proposition which states that two species competing for the same resources cannot coexist if other ecological factors are constant.
